HEADWORD: Lazulite
<hw>Laz"u*lite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>lazuli</ets> : cf. F. <ets>lazulite</ets>, G.
<ets>lazulith</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral of a light
indigo-blue color, occurring in small masses, or in monoclinic crystals;
blue spar. It is a hydrous phosphate of alumina and magnesia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

